values:
after graduation
all the younglings are forgotten
as the graduates go on
to a better place..

nobody listens
nobody stays
nobody seems to care
nobody remembers
everyone forgets
and no one stays gold
cause only gold stays.

i wish all of you graduates the best of luck
and the best of karma.
i wish i could tell you i'll miss you
and remember you always,
but then i'd expect you to say it back
and i dont want to hear your faulse truthes any longer.

goodbye my once dear friends
goodnight our gay dally
goodnight forevermore
blessed be my dear ones

Makes me feel like I can't trust you,
like I'm not safe with you. 
You know my beliefs 
yet you don't honor them. 
You don't respect them; 
or me. 
The number of people I can really trust 
is drastically decreasing. 
I don't like feeling like I want to beat the shit out of my friends. 
You don't understand how you hurt me 
all the time. 
Then when you know you've hurt me, 
do you bother to change it? 
To make it right? 
No, 
you just go about your lives. 
Don't bother to say you love me, 
or that you care, 
cause I know you don't.

Moon shines down on 
The wilderness around me
A beautiful moon

Like a flashlights,
The eyes of the little cat,
Shine in the window
Mysteriously starring at you
Like a queen of royalty
Shinning the color of the sea
Glimmering in the sun
Little cat.

sitting at a point, 
between the two legs of hall, 
surounded by windows, 
i sat at my table. 
lunch period, 
not that i was eating. 
writing. 
i sat alone 
in my quiet corner. 
then voices cracked my silence. 
they grew, 
till they were about to pass. 
i didnt look up. 
"hey cutie" 
came a dialect twisted voice. 
i didnt look up, 
pretended i didnt hear. 
"eww, 
that's sick man!" another replied to his friend. 
i felt my cheeks flush, 
but i didnt look up. 
their voices begain to get more distant. 
i waited till they were arond a corner 
before raising my head. 
i looked at my reflection in the glass window. 
"'sick'....
so this is sick..."

im alone
forever alone in a room
no one wants to talk to me
no one seems to care
night after night i sit here daring myself to make a move...
but i dont
im pathetic, you know it?
i cant even hurt myself anymore
the pain of the cutting on my chest hardly hurts anymore
i dont get phone calls
i dont get emails
i dont even get instant messeges anymore
im alone
forever alone in a room
i stare out the window at the children playing in the street
and sigh
why cant i be like that?
why cant i have friends that always want me and love me
why cant i have more than that like everyone else?
is it because im too annoying?
strange?
depressed?
emotional?
ugly?
for you?
or do you just not like me?
maybe you just dont like me
maybe im just not a likeable person
im alone
forever alone in a room...
did i mention i was alone?

My skirt is smeared with blood
I never ment to spill,
I hate the one I love
The one I never ment to kill.
I hate the thought, of what I thought could've been
But really never will..
I waited so long 
Just to hear I didnt fit
And I guess i never will...
